---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="How We Work — Skief Labs" description="Structured work. No chaos. No dependency. Learn how Skief Labs approaches every engagement with clarity and restraint.">
  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="bg-linen py-24 md:py-36">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <h1 class="heading-serif text-4xl md:text-6xl lg:text-7xl text-navy-900 mb-8">
          Structured work. No chaos. No dependency.
        </h1>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-navy-900/80 text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
          <p>Most automation and systems projects fail not because the technology is wrong — but because the process around it is absent.</p>
          <p>Tools get added before problems are understood. Systems get built without documentation. Clients are left dependent on the people who built them.</p>
          <p>Our way of working exists to prevent exactly that.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- THE PRINCIPLES -->
  <section class="section-dark py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="mb-16">
        <p class="subhead-condensed text-sm text-blue-500 mb-4">Our Principles</p>
        <p class="text-linen/60 text-base md:text-lg max-w-xl">
          These apply to every engagement, regardless of size or service.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-x-12 gap-y-16">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-linen text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Diagnosis before prescription</h3>
          <p class="text-linen/70 text-base leading-relaxed">
            We don't recommend solutions before we understand the problem. This sounds obvious. In practice, most vendors skip it.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-linen text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Judgment before automation</h3>
          <p class="text-linen/70 text-base leading-relaxed">
            Not everything should be automated. We're deliberate about what stays human — and why. Restraint is part of what you're hiring.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-linen text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Clarity over complexity</h3>
          <p class="text-linen/70 text-base leading-relaxed">
            If a system can't be explained simply, it isn't finished. Every workflow we build can be understood by the people who use it.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-linen text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Ownership by design</h3>
          <p class="text-linen/70 text-base leading-relaxed">
            Nothing we build should require us to stay involved. Full documentation, clean handoff, zero dependency — by default, not on request.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="md:col-span-2">
          <h3 class="text-linen text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Fixed scope. Fixed expectations.</h3>
          <p class="text-linen/70 text-base leading-relaxed max-w-xl">
            No drifting projects. No surprise invoices. No open-ended engagements that expand without your consent.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- THE ENGAGEMENT -->
  <section class="bg-linen py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="heading-serif text-3xl md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl text-navy-900 mb-4">
          The Engagement
        </h2>
        <p class="text-navy-900/70 text-base md:text-lg max-w-xl">
          Once there's a clear fit, the path differs by service — but the principles are the same.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 lg:gap-12">
        <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-8 md:p-10 border border-navy-900/5">
          <h3 class="subhead-condensed text-sm text-blue-500 mb-4">For Data Intelligence</h3>
          <div class="space-y-4 text-navy-900/80 text-base leading-relaxed">
            <p>We scope the build based on what the discovery conversation reveals. Work is fixed in scope, time-bound, and fully documented.</p>
            <p>At completion, you own the system entirely — transferred access, clean documentation, logic any competent partner or internal hire could maintain.</p>
            <p>Some clients have us continue operating the system on an ongoing basis. Others take it and run it themselves. Either way is fine. The goal was never dependency.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-8 md:p-10 border border-navy-900/5">
          <h3 class="subhead-condensed text-sm text-blue-500 mb-4">For Sales Acceleration</h3>
          <div class="space-y-4 text-navy-900/80 text-base leading-relaxed">
            <p>We start with a pilot — a defined scope and fixed price that builds the system and runs it through the first weeks of live execution.</p>
            <p>Most clients move to an ongoing monthly retainer from there, where we continue running and optimizing the outbound motion.</p>
            <p>There's no obligation to continue beyond the pilot, and no lock-in at any point. The system — and everything in it — remains yours.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-navy-900/60 text-base mt-8 max-w-2xl">
        In both cases: nothing is built before the scope is clear. No surprises mid-engagement. No invoices for work you didn't agree to.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHAT WORKING WITH US FEELS LIKE -->
  <section class="section-dark py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <h2 class="heading-serif text-3xl md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl text-linen mb-8">
          What working with us feels like
        </h2>
        <p class="text-linen text-xl md:text-2xl font-serif italic mb-8">
          Clients describe it as calm.
        </p>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-linen/80 text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed">
          <p>There are no status meetings held for the sake of appearances. No performative reporting designed to justify the invoice. No pressure to expand scope beyond what makes sense.</p>
          <p>You'll always know what we're doing and why. Decisions are explained, not handed down. Progress is visible, not summarized at the end of the month.</p>
          <p class="text-linen font-semibold">We build what needs to exist — and stop.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="bg-linen py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary">Book a 30-minute discovery call</a>
      <p class="text-navy-900/50 text-sm mt-3 italic">No pitch. No obligation. Just clarity.</p>
      <p class="text-navy-900/40 text-sm mt-8 italic font-serif">More business. Less busyness.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
